{
  "texts": [
    "It reflects how well the isolated labels separate from other cell identities, ranging from 0 to 1, where 1 means all the isolated label cells and no others are grouped into one cluster.Graph cLISI.",
    "The graph cLISI is similar to the graph iLISI but focuses on cell-type labels rather than batch labels.",
    "Unlike iLISI that highlights the mixing of groups, cLISI values the separation of groups 61.",
    "The graph-adjusted cLISI is scaled to [0, 1], with a value of 0 corresponding to low cell-type separation and a value of 1 corresponding to strong cell-type separation.Overall scores. scIB.",
    "We compute the scIB overall score using the batch correction and biological conservation metrics defined either on the embedding space (for algorithms generating embeddings or graphs) or the feature space (for algorithms generating batch-corrected features)."
  ]
}